This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it proposes a new approach for parallelizing Bayesian optimization using Gaussian Process bandit optimization, which is a popular machine learning technique. The paper also discusses hyper-parameter optimization, which is a common problem in machine learning. 

It is also likely to belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the proposed method involves modeling the diversity of a batch via Determinantal point processes (DPPs), which is a technique commonly used in AI for modeling diversity. 

The paper's experiments involve robotics and computer vision tasks, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) and cs.RO (Robotics). 

Finally, the paper's focus on optimization and regret bounds suggests that it could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
